			Researchwork
			
			IfocusontheresearchonfunctionalgenesofMagnaportheoryzae.WetrytoanalyzethemachineryoftheautophagyinM.oryzae.
AnovelmethodforpurificationoftotalRNAfromM.oryzaeappressoriaofhasbeendevelopedinourlab.ThetotalRNAofappressoriawasisolateddirectlyfromtheappressoriaofthisfungusinoculatedonahydrophobicsurfaceofprojectiontransparencyfilmwithTrizolreagent.WehadsuccessfullyobtainedthetotalRNAofM.oryzaefromtheappressoriaincubated(fromconidia)for2,4,8,12,18,24and30handbuiltmatureappressoriumcDNAlibraries.TotalRNAoftheconidia/aerialmycelia/substratemyceliamixtureandthematureappressoriaattheincubationof23.5~24.5hwereisolated.AsubtractiveappressoriacDNAlibrary,subtractedbytheconidia/aerialmycelia/substratemyceliamixture,wasconstructedbysuppressionsubtractivehybridization(SSH).MgATG1gene,homologueofATG1,wasselectedfromtheSSHlibrary.
Currently,IfocusonautophagyprocessinM.oryzae.Disruptionofautophagyrelatedgenes,suchasMgATG1,MgATG2,MgATG4,etc.,involvedintheautophagypathway,influencedthecapabilityofsurvivingstarvation,conidiation,conidialgermination,lipidturnover,andappressoriumturgorgeneration.Asaresult,thesenullmutantslosetheirpenetrationandpathogenicityintothehostplants.However,targeteddeletionofMgATG11,MgATG13andMgATG17homologoustoATG11,ATG13andATG17inyeastrespectively,didnotblockautophagypathwayinM.oryzae.However,whenwedoubleknock-outMgATG11andMgATG17,MgATG13andMgATG17,thepathogenicitywasreducedsignificantly.

			
				
